Are you a first-year student enrolled in a political science course? Interested in getting involved in student government? Consider running to become one of two First-Year Representatives for the APSS!

The Association of Political Science Students (APSS) is the official Departmental course union that represents all undergraduate students enrolled in political science courses. 

As First-Year Representative, you and your co-Representative are in charge of organizing events for first-years, representing first-years’ interests at meetings, and reaching out to other first-years in political science.

Any first-year student who has taken or is currently enrolled in a political science course is eligible to run to be a First-Year Representative!

Fill out the Google forms in our LinkTree to nominate yourself. Elections will take place on Monday, September 30th from 5-6PM over Zoom.

CSBSU Mentorship Program 2024 - Applications Open!
Ready to kick off the school year with guidance and community? We're now recruiting mentees from years 1 and 2, and mentors from years 3 and up! Apply by Friday, October 11th, at 11:59 PM ET to be matched with an amazing mentor or mentee for the year.

Mentees can gain valuable advice on navigating their early undergrad experience, while mentors have the chance to develop leadership and communication skills. With exciting events and activities planned, both mentees and mentors will benefit—and all participants will earn CCR credit!

HEY FSAT! As we say goodbye to the third return of Sama-Summer, we tried to sum up all the fun into three minutes (it wasn’t easy). 

But if there’s one thing we learned, it’s not a Filipino function without any karaoke!!

Competitiveness lies in the Filipino genes fr 😌 BRING ME, A PLUSHIEEE 

We saw some of y’all bonded with iconic dances! Based off of emergency budots, now we really have proof of who to call in an emergency 🤳. 

On top of that we had “maybe this time”, “tiramisu cake”, and “touch” — we can easilyyy form a p-pop group 👀 

We hope you enjoyed our games!! We shall see you all soon, have an amazing start to your school years everyone 🫶🏼

Much love,
Pionah and Victoria <3

Want to sign up for Technical Interview Night, but not sure what the hype is all about? Keep reading to find out more!

Technical Interview Night, or TIN, is an evening for students looking for PEY placements to practice their interview skills and get resume advice from real recruiters and managers from industry. 

On top of getting technical interview experience, you’ll also have the chance to ask recruiters any questions you may have. There will also be plenty of free food and networking as well!! Spots are limited, so be sure to sign up through the link in our bio!

Technical Interview Night is dedicated to giving students the opportunity to network with industry professionals and practice their interview skills through mock-interviews hosted by real recruiters. 

Applications to attend TIN are now open through the link in our bio, but be sure to sign up early as spots are limited!

Join us while we create and reflect on Orange Shirt Day, which is observed on September 30th. Orange Shirt Day has been observed annually for many years, and since 2021, has been formally recognized as the National Day for Truth & Reconciliation. 

We look forward to engaging in critical conversations around the topics of truth and reconciliation, decolonization, and Indigenous justice. We hope that you can join us. 

#TruthandReconciliation #OrangeShirtDay #IndigenousJustice #TRC2024 #TRC #OISEGSA #StudentsonSeven #AECD #AdultEducation #OISE #OISEUofT

Hello OISE students, 

Below is a message from The Varsity Reporter, Jessie Schwalb:

In April, OISE got hit with a ransomware attack that leaked SIN numbers for more than 8,200 students, alumni, and personnel. My name is Jessie Schwalb, and I'm a reporter from The Varsity who's looking into this attack. If you or anyone you know got an email telling you that the attack exposed your data and you'd be willing to speak a bit about your experience, please contact me at jessies@thevarsity.ca. Thank you for supporting student journalism!

Please contact @thevarsitypublications reporter Jessie Schwalb by SEPTEMBER 25 if the April ransomware incident impacted you or people you know! 
DM on IG: @j.smidgeon 
Email: jessies@thevarsity.ca
Thanks for supporting student journalism!
